#. <section class="sutta" id="sn21.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn21.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 21"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 21"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhuvagga"
msgstr "1. Monks"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 7. Visākhasutta → visākhapañcāliputtasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn21.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Visākhasutta"
msgstr "7. With Visākha, Pañcāli’s Son"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.280"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.7:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn21.7:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

#. VAR: visākho pañcālaputto → visākho pañcāliputto (bj)
msgctxt "sn21.7:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā visākho pañcālaputto upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ bhikkhū "
"dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti, poriyā "
"vācāya vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāya."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Visākha, Pañcāli’s son, was educating, "
"encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the mendicants in the assembly hall "
"with a Dhamma talk. His words were polished, clear, articulate, expressing "
"the meaning, comprehensive, and independent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.7:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena upaṭṭhānasālā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the "
"assembly hall. He sat down on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "sn21.7:2.2"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn21.7:2.3"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhikkhave, upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandasseti "
"samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti poriyā vācāya vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya "
"atthassa viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, who was educating, encouraging, firing up, and inspiring the "
"mendicants in the assembly hall with a Dhamma talk?”"

msgctxt "sn21.7:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Āyasmā, bhante, visākho pañcālaputto upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ bhikkhū dhammiyā "
"kathāya sandasseti samādapeti samuttejeti sampahaṃseti, poriyā vācāya "
"vissaṭṭhāya anelagalāya atthassa viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāyā”ti."
msgstr "“Sir, it was Venerable Visākha, Pañcāli’s son.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.7:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ visākhaṃ pañcālaputtaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Visākha:"

msgctxt "sn21.7:3.2"
msgid "“sādhu sādhu, visākha,"
msgstr "“Good, good, Visākha!"

msgctxt "sn21.7:3.3"
msgid ""
"sādhu kho tvaṃ, visākha, bhikkhū dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi … pe … atthassa "
"viññāpaniyā pariyāpannāya anissitāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s good that you educate, encourage, fire up, and inspire the mendicants "
"in the assembly hall with a Dhamma talk, with words that are polished, "
"clear, articulate, expressing the meaning, comprehensive, and independent.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.7:4.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn21.7:4.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.7:5.1"
msgid "“Nābhāsamānaṃ jānanti,"
msgstr "“Though an astute person is mixed up with fools,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.7:5.2"
msgid "missaṃ bālehi paṇḍitaṃ;"
msgstr "they don’t know unless he speaks."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.7:5.3"
msgid "Bhāsamānañca jānanti,"
msgstr "But when he speaks they know,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.7:5.4"
msgid "desentaṃ amataṃ padaṃ."
msgstr "he’s teaching the deathless state."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn21.7:6.1"
msgid "Bhāsaye jotaye dhammaṃ,"
msgstr "He should speak and illustrate the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.7:6.2"
msgid "paggaṇhe isinaṃ dhajaṃ;"
msgstr "holding up the banner of the hermits."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.7:6.3"
msgid "Subhāsitadhajā isayo,"
msgstr "Words well spoken are the hermits’ banner,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn21.7:6.4"
msgid "dhammo hi isinaṃ dhajo”ti."
msgstr "for the teaching is the banner of the hermits.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn21.7:6.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
